notes.note:
Hello Craig,

The customers complaint was the engine overheated and went into limp mode.
Upon arrival the vehicle was very low on coolant. 
On the previous visit a block test was performed. The vehicle passed two tests.
The coolant was topped up, cooling system was bled and an engine block test was performed. 
The engine failed the block test noting exhaust gas getting into the cooling system.
These engines are very bad for cylinder head cracks. 
The failure to the engine would be cylinder head malfunction(cracked)
Cylinder heads on these engines fail in great numbers as I'm sure your aware
The issue with replacing the cylinder head is its time consuming and most of the time coolant has entered the engine oil.
This in the future will cause major issues for longevity.
Many of these have came back after doing just the cylinder head and gaskets when customers are on a budget with the lower end of the engine failed because of previous coolant in the oil.
There is no warranty from Ford for the cylinder head or gaskets. We have been through this.
Warranty on the used engine is 30 days parts only.
The recyclers do not want to warranty past that.
Extra warranty may be available but at a significant increase in price for the engine.

Best regards
Mark Robinso
